sentences: Herb Jaffe (May 20, 1921 – December 7, 1991) was an independent film producer in the United States.

He was born in Brooklyn, New York, and began his career as a literary agent, working for the likes of: Paddy Chayefsky   – Marty (1955), The Hospital (1971) and Network (1976), Reginald Rose   – Twelve Angry Men (1954), Joseph Heller   – Catch-22 (1961), Something Happened (1974) and Philip Roth   – Goodbye, Columbus (1959), Portnoy's Complaint (1969), American Pastoral (1997), The Human Stain (2001).
Some of his other films include: Who'll Stop the Rain with Nick Nolte, Jinxed! with Bette Midler, The Demon Seed with Julie Christie, Time After Time and Fright Night Part 2 with Julie Carmen.
